 Docker Microservices Architecture
Objectives
Design and deploy a multi-service containerized application using Docker and Docker Compose, with each service independently buildable and runnable
Implement inter-service HTTP communication across a custom Docker bridge network, where one service calls another by container name
Expose all services through a single API Gateway container that routes requests, enforces rate limiting, and returns structured error responses when a backend is unreachable
Prerequisites
Comfortable navigating and editing files on a Linux/Ubuntu system using the command line
Familiar with REST API concepts: HTTP methods, status codes, and JSON request/response bodies
Lab Environment
You will work on a dedicated AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance provided by Al Nafi. The instance has a base Ubuntu installation; you will install all required tools in Task 1.

